article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 86, Wiley 49
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Brandon Cutler scored 16 points and Denzel Barnes added 14 to lead Stephen F. Austin to an 86-49 victory over Wiley on Monday night. Jordan Glynn added 11 points and Mark Gomillia had 10 for the Lumberjacks (9-3), who outrebounded the Wildcats 40-21. Marquis Wright scored 19 points to lead Wiley (7-6), an NAIA team. No other player reached double figures for the Wildcats. Stephen F. Austin trailed 7-6 before taking the lead for good with a 12-0 run. The Lumberjacks increased their advantage to 39-23 at halftime and led by 38 in the second half. Cutler was 5 of 6 from the floor, helping the Lumberjacks shot 53.6 percent, and 6 of 6 from the foul line.
